    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-08-08T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-08-08T10:00:00-05:00" n="275"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d275">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">353/8–850: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d275fn1">Repeated to the United States Mission at the United
                        Nations (<gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss>) as No. 121 and the Embassy
                        in South Africa for information only as No. 17.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-08-08T11:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1950—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>690. Dept holding conversation Jooste<note n="2" xml:id="d275fn2">G. P. Jooste,
                        Ambassador of the Union of South Africa in the United States.</note> here
                    Aug 7<note n="3" xml:id="d275fn3">This telegram was drafted on August 7. For a
                        report of the conversation, see Department’s telegram 18, August 9, to
                        Pretoria, <ref target="#pg_477">p. 477</ref>.</note> 1) ascertain <gloss
                        target="#t_SOAFR1">SoAfr</gloss> plans respecting submission reports on
                        <gloss target="#t_SWASWAFR1">SW Afr</gloss> pursuant <gloss target="#t_ICJ1"
                        >ICJ</gloss> opinion, 2) encourage <gloss target="#t_SOAFR1">SoAfr</gloss>
                    indicate at 5th <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> its willingness report on
                        <gloss target="#t_SWASWAFR1">SW Afr</gloss>, 3) discuss <gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> machinery for examining reports. In Dept’s
                    opinion Aug 30 elections <gloss target="#t_SWASWAFR1">SW Afr</gloss> require
                    immediate approach to avoid possibility extreme statements during election
                    campaign. Types of possible <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> machinery to
                    examine reports include TO, new comite <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>
                    <pb facs="0492" n="476" xml:id="pg_476"/> established especially for purpose,
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> 4th Comite, comite experts like Mandates
                    Comm chosen by and reporting to <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> or <gloss
                        target="#t_TC1">TC</gloss>. Dept will emphasize importance of <gloss
                        target="#t_SOAFR1">SoAfr</gloss> taking action in accordance <gloss
                        target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss> opinion to forestall castigation in <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>, prevent <gloss target="#t_SOAFR1">SoAfr</gloss>
                    isolation in <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>, and, in view present <gloss
                        target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss> crisis,<note n="4" xml:id="d275fn4">This is a
                        reference to the outbreak of the war in Korea; for documentation on this
                        subject, see volume <hi rend="smallcaps">vii</hi>.</note> avoid sharp
                    divergencies with Asian nations in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Pls discuss with UK Govt with objective obtaining UK support for Dept’s efforts
                    encourage <gloss target="#t_SOAFR1">SoAfr</gloss> submit reports pursuant <gloss
                        target="#t_ICJ1">ICJ</gloss> opinion. Telegraph reactions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
